{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I spent the better part of a decade"},{"time":3000,"text":"looking at American responses to mass atrocity and genocide."},{"time":9000,"text":"And I'd like to start by sharing with you one moment"},{"time":15000,"text":"that to me sums up what there is to know"},{"time":18000,"text":"about American and democratic responses to mass atrocity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"And that moment came on April 21, 1994."},{"time":27000,"text":"So 14 years ago, almost, in the middle of the Rwandan genocide,"},{"time":31000,"text":"in which 800,000 people would be systematically exterminated"},{"time":36000,"text":"by the Rwandan government and some extremist militia."},{"time":41000,"text":"On April 21, in the New York Times,"},{"time":45000,"text":"the paper reported that somewhere between 200,000 and 300,000 people"},{"time":48000,"text":"had already been killed in the genocide."},{"time":51000,"text":"It was in the paper -- not on the front page."},{"time":54000,"text":"It was a lot like the Holocaust coverage,"},{"time":56000,"text":"it was buried in the paper."},{"time":58000,"text":"Rwanda itself was not seen as newsworthy,"},{"time":60000,"text":"and amazingly, genocide itself was not seen as newsworthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"But on April 21, a wonderfully honest moment occurred."},{"time":68000,"text":"And that was that an American congresswoman"},{"time":71000,"text":"named Patricia Schroeder from Colorado"},{"time":73000,"text":"met with a group of journalists."},{"time":75000,"text":"And one of the journalists said to her, what's up?"},{"time":79000,"text":"What's going on in the U.S. government?"},{"time":81000,"text":"Two to 300,000 people have just been exterminated"},{"time":83000,"text":"in the last couple of weeks in Rwanda."},{"time":85000,"text":"It's two weeks into the genocide at that time,"},{"time":87000,"text":"but of course, at that time you don't know how long it's going to last."},{"time":90000,"text":"And the journalist said, why is there so little response out of Washington?"},{"time":95000,"text":"Why no hearings, no denunciations,"},{"time":98000,"text":"no people getting arrested in front of the Rwandan embassy"},{"time":101000,"text":"or in front of the White House? What's the deal?"},{"time":105000,"text":"And she said -- she was so honest -- she said, \"It's a great question."},{"time":110000,"text":"All I can tell you is that in my congressional office in Colorado"},{"time":114000,"text":"and my office in Washington,"},{"time":116000,"text":"we're getting hundreds and hundreds of calls"},{"time":119000,"text":"about the endangered ape and gorilla population in Rwanda,"},{"time":124000,"text":"but nobody is calling about the people."},{"time":127000,"text":"The phones just aren't ringing about the people.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"And the reason I give you this moment is there's a deep truth in it."},{"time":135000,"text":"And that truth is, or was, in the 20th century,"},{"time":139000,"text":"that while we were beginning to develop endangered species movements, \n"},{"time":144000,"text":"we didn't have an endangered people's movement."},{"time":146000,"text":"We had Holocaust education in the schools."},{"time":150000,"text":"Most of us were groomed not only on images of nuclear catastrophe,"},{"time":154000,"text":"but also on images and knowledge of the Holocaust."},{"time":159000,"text":"There's a museum, of course, on the Mall in Washington,"},{"time":162000,"text":"right next to Lincoln and Jefferson."},{"time":164000,"text":"I mean, we have owned Never Again culturally,"},{"time":168000,"text":"appropriately, interestingly."},{"time":172000,"text":"And yet the politicization of Never Again,"},{"time":176000,"text":"the operationalization of Never Again,"},{"time":178000,"text":"had never occurred in the 20th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"And that's what that moment with Patricia Schroeder I think shows:"},{"time":184000,"text":"that if we are to bring about an end to the world's worst atrocities,"},{"time":191000,"text":"we have to make it such."},{"time":193000,"text":"There has to be a role --"},{"time":195000,"text":"there has to be the creation of political noise and political costs"},{"time":198000,"text":"in response to massive crimes against humanity, and so forth."},{"time":201000,"text":"So that was the 20th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"Now here -- and this will be a relief to you at this point in the afternoon --"},{"time":207000,"text":"there is good news, amazing news, in the 21st century,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and that is that, almost out of nowhere, there has come into being"},{"time":218000,"text":"an anti-genocide movement, an anti-genocide constituency,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and one that looks destined, in fact, to be permanent."},{"time":225000,"text":"It grew up in response to the atrocities in Darfur."},{"time":228000,"text":"It is comprised of students. There are something like 300 anti-genocide chapters"},{"time":234000,"text":"on college campuses around the country."},{"time":237000,"text":"It's bigger than the anti-apartheid movement."},{"time":239000,"text":"There are something like 500 high school chapters"},{"time":243000,"text":"devoted to stopping the genocide in Darfur."},{"time":246000,"text":"Evangelicals have joined it. Jewish groups have joined it."},{"time":250000,"text":"\"Hotel Rwanda\" watchers have joined it. It is a cacophonous movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254000,"text":"To call it a movement, as with all movements, perhaps, is a little misleading."},{"time":257000,"text":"It's diverse. It's got a lot of different approaches."},{"time":260000,"text":"It's got all the ups and the downs of movements."},{"time":262000,"text":"But it has been amazingly successful in one regard,"},{"time":266000,"text":"in that it has become,"},{"time":268000,"text":"it has congealed into this endangered people's movement"},{"time":271000,"text":"that was missing in the 20th century."},{"time":273000,"text":"It sees itself, such as it is, the it,"},{"time":276000,"text":"as something that will create the impression that there will be political cost,"},{"time":281000,"text":"there will be a political price to be paid,"},{"time":284000,"text":"for allowing genocide, for not having an heroic imagination,"},{"time":288000,"text":"for not being an upstander but for being, in fact, a bystander."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"Now because it's student-driven,"},{"time":296000,"text":"there's some amazing things that the movement has done."},{"time":298000,"text":"They have launched a divestment campaign"},{"time":300000,"text":"that has now convinced, I think, 55 universities in 22 states"},{"time":304000,"text":"to divest their holdings of stocks"},{"time":306000,"text":"with regard to companies doing business in Sudan."},{"time":310000,"text":"They have a 1-800-GENOCIDE number --"},{"time":312000,"text":"this is going to sound very kitsch,"},{"time":314000,"text":"but for those of you who may not be, I mean, may be apolitical,"},{"time":318000,"text":"but interested in doing something about genocide,"},{"time":320000,"text":"you dial 1-800-GENOCIDE and you type in your zip code,"},{"time":323000,"text":"and you don't even have to know who your congressperson is."},{"time":325000,"text":"It will refer you directly to your congressperson, to your U.S. senator,"},{"time":329000,"text":"to your governor where divestment legislation is pending."},{"time":332000,"text":"They've lowered the transaction costs of stopping genocide."},{"time":336000,"text":"I think the most innovative thing they've introduced recently"},{"time":339000,"text":"are genocide grades."},{"time":342000,"text":"And it takes students to introduce genocide grades."},{"time":345000,"text":"So what you now have when a Congress is in session"},{"time":348000,"text":"is members of Congress calling up these 19-year-olds or 24-year-olds"},{"time":353000,"text":"and saying, I'm just told I have a D minus on genocide;"},{"time":356000,"text":"what do I do to get a C? I just want to get a C. Help me."},{"time":360000,"text":"And the students and the others"},{"time":362000,"text":"who are part of this incredibly energized base"},{"time":364000,"text":"are there to answer that, and there's always something to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"Now, what this movement has done is it has extracted from the Bush administration"},{"time":373000,"text":"from the United States,"},{"time":375000,"text":"at a time of massive over-stretch -- military, financial, diplomatic --"},{"time":380000,"text":"a whole series of commitments to Darfur"},{"time":382000,"text":"that no other country in the world is making."},{"time":385000,"text":"For instance, the referral of the crimes in Darfur"},{"time":387000,"text":"to the International Criminal Court,"},{"time":389000,"text":"which the Bush administration doesn't like."},{"time":391000,"text":"The expenditure of 3 billion dollars in refugee camps to try to keep,"},{"time":395000,"text":"basically, the people who've been displaced from their homes"},{"time":397000,"text":"by the Sudanese government, by the so-called Janjaweed, the militia,"},{"time":400000,"text":"to keep those people alive"},{"time":402000,"text":"until something more durable can be achieved."},{"time":406000,"text":"And recently, or now not that recently,"},{"time":408000,"text":"about six months ago, the authorization of a peacekeeping force"},{"time":411000,"text":"of 26,000 that will go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"And that's all the Bush administration's leadership,"},{"time":415000,"text":"and it's all because of this bottom-up pressure"},{"time":417000,"text":"and the fact that the phones haven't stopped ringing"},{"time":420000,"text":"from the beginning of this crisis."},{"time":422000,"text":"The bad news, however, to this question of will evil prevail,"},{"time":425000,"text":"is that evil lives on."},{"time":427000,"text":"The people in those camps are surrounded on all sides"},{"time":431000,"text":"by so-called Janjaweed, these men on horseback"},{"time":433000,"text":"with spears and Kalashnikovs."},{"time":435000,"text":"Women who go to get firewood in order to heat the humanitarian aid"},{"time":439000,"text":"in order to feed their families -- humanitarian aid,"},{"time":442000,"text":"the dirty secret of it is it has to be heated, really, to be edible --"},{"time":445000,"text":"are themselves subjected to rape,"},{"time":447000,"text":"which is a tool of the genocide that is being used."},{"time":449000,"text":"And the peacekeepers I've mentioned, the force has been authorized,"},{"time":452000,"text":"but almost no country on Earth has stepped forward since the authorization"},{"time":457000,"text":"to actually put its troops or its police in harm's way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460000,"text":"So we have achieved an awful lot relative to the 20th century,"},{"time":465000,"text":"and yet far too little relative to the gravity of the crime that is unfolding"},{"time":469000,"text":"as we sit here, as we speak."},{"time":471000,"text":"Why the limits to the movement?"},{"time":474000,"text":"Why is what has been achieved, or what the movement has done,"},{"time":478000,"text":"been necessary but not sufficient to the crime?"},{"time":480000,"text":"I think there are a couple -- there are many reasons --"},{"time":482000,"text":"but a couple just to focus on briefly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"The first is that the movement, such as it is,\n"},{"time":488000,"text":"stops at America's borders. \nIt is not a global movement. \n"},{"time":492000,"text":"It does not have too many compatriots abroad who themselves"},{"time":496000,"text":"are asking their governments to do more to stop genocide."},{"time":500000,"text":"And the Holocaust culture that we have in this country"},{"time":502000,"text":"makes Americans, sort of, more prone to, I think,"},{"time":505000,"text":"want to bring Never Again to life."},{"time":508000,"text":"The guilt that the Clinton administration expressed,"},{"time":512000,"text":"that Bill Clinton expressed over Rwanda,"},{"time":514000,"text":"created a space in our society for a consensus"},{"time":516000,"text":"that Rwanda was bad and wrong"},{"time":518000,"text":"and we wish we had done more, and that is something"},{"time":520000,"text":"that the movement has taken advantage of."},{"time":522000,"text":"European governments, for the most part,"},{"time":523000,"text":"haven't acknowledged responsibility, and there's nothing to kind of"},{"time":526000,"text":"to push back and up against."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"So this movement, if it's to be durable and global,"},{"time":534000,"text":"will have to cross borders, and you will have to see"},{"time":537000,"text":"other citizens in democracies, not simply resting on the assumption"},{"time":541000,"text":"that their government would do something in the face of genocide,"},{"time":544000,"text":"but actually making it such."},{"time":546000,"text":"Governments will never gravitate towards crimes of this magnitude"},{"time":549000,"text":"naturally or eagerly."},{"time":551000,"text":"As we saw, they haven't even gravitated towards protecting our ports"},{"time":553000,"text":"or reigning in loose nukes."},{"time":555000,"text":"Why would we expect in a bureaucracy that it would orient itself"},{"time":559000,"text":"towards distant suffering?"},{"time":561000,"text":"So one reason is it hasn't gone global."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"The second is, of course, that at this time in particular in America's history,"},{"time":567000,"text":"we have a credibility problem,"},{"time":569000,"text":"a legitimacy problem in international institutions."},{"time":571000,"text":"It is structurally really, really hard to do,"},{"time":574000,"text":"as the Bush administration rightly does,"},{"time":576000,"text":"which is to denounce genocide on a Monday"},{"time":580000,"text":"and then describe water boarding on a Tuesday as a no-brainer"},{"time":583000,"text":"and then turn up on Wednesday and look for troop commitments."},{"time":587000,"text":"Now, other countries have their own reasons for not wanting to get involved."},{"time":590000,"text":"Let me be clear."},{"time":592000,"text":"They're in some ways using the Bush administration as an alibi."},{"time":595000,"text":"But it is essential for us to be a leader in this sphere,"},{"time":599000,"text":"of course to restore our standing and our leadership in the world."},{"time":603000,"text":"The recovery's going to take some time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605000,"text":"We have to ask ourselves, what now? What do we do going forward"},{"time":608000,"text":"as a country and as citizens in relationship to the world's worst places,"},{"time":612000,"text":"the world's worst suffering, killers, and the kinds of killers"},{"time":617000,"text":"that could come home to roost sometime in the future?"},{"time":622000,"text":"The place that I turned to answer that question was to a man"},{"time":628000,"text":"that many of you may not have ever heard of,"},{"time":631000,"text":"and that is a Brazilian named Sergio Vieira de Mello who,"},{"time":636000,"text":"as Chris said, was blown up in Iraq in 2003."},{"time":642000,"text":"He was the victim of the first-ever suicide bomb in Iraq."},{"time":645000,"text":"It's hard to remember, but there was actually a time in the summer of 2003,"},{"time":648000,"text":"even after the U.S. invasion, where,"},{"time":651000,"text":"apart from looting, civilians were relatively safe in Iraq."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655000,"text":"Now, who was Sergio? Sergio Vieira de Mello was his name."},{"time":658000,"text":"In addition to being Brazilian, he was described to me"},{"time":661000,"text":"before I met him in 1994 as someone who was a cross between"},{"time":664000,"text":"James Bond on the one hand and Bobby Kennedy on the other."},{"time":668000,"text":"And in the U.N., you don't get that many people"},{"time":671000,"text":"who actually manage to merge those qualities."},{"time":674000,"text":"He was James Bond-like in that he was ingenious."},{"time":678000,"text":"He was drawn to the flames, he chased the flames,"},{"time":681000,"text":"he was like a moth to the flames. Something of an adrenalin junkie."},{"time":684000,"text":"He was successful with women."},{"time":689000,"text":"He was Bobby Kennedy-like because in some ways one could never tell"},{"time":693000,"text":"if he was a realist masquerading as an idealist"},{"time":695000,"text":"or an idealist masquerading as a realist, as people always wondered"},{"time":699000,"text":"about Bobby Kennedy and John Kennedy in that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"What he was was a decathlete of nation-building, of problem-solving,"},{"time":706000,"text":"of troubleshooting in the world's worst places"},{"time":709000,"text":"and in the world's most broken places."},{"time":712000,"text":"In failing states, genocidal states, under-governed states,"},{"time":716000,"text":"precisely the kinds of places that threats to this country exist"},{"time":721000,"text":"on the horizon, and precisely the kinds of places"},{"time":724000,"text":"where most of the world's suffering tends to get concentrated."},{"time":728000,"text":"These are the places he was drawn to."},{"time":730000,"text":"He moved with the headlines."},{"time":732000,"text":"He was in the U.N. for 34 years. He joined at the age of 21."},{"time":737000,"text":"Started off when the causes in the wars du jour in the '70s"},{"time":740000,"text":"were wars of independence and decolonization."},{"time":742000,"text":"He was there in Bangladesh"},{"time":744000,"text":"dealing with the outflow of millions of refugees --"},{"time":746000,"text":"the largest refugee flow in history up to that point."},{"time":749000,"text":"He was in Sudan when the civil war broke out there."},{"time":752000,"text":"He was in Cyprus right after the Turkish invasion."},{"time":755000,"text":"He was in Mozambique for the War of Independence."},{"time":757000,"text":"He was in Lebanon. Amazingly, he was in Lebanon -- the U.N. base was used --"},{"time":760000,"text":"Palestinians staged attacks out from behind the U.N. base."},{"time":764000,"text":"Israel then invaded and overran the U.N. base."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"Sergio was in Beirut when the U.S. Embassy was hit"},{"time":769000,"text":"by the first-ever suicide attack against the United States. \n"},{"time":772000,"text":"People date the beginning of this new era to 9/11, but surely 1983,"},{"time":777000,"text":"with the attack on the US Embassy and the Marine barracks --"},{"time":779000,"text":"which Sergio witnessed -- those are, in fact, in some ways,"},{"time":782000,"text":"the dawning of the era that we find ourselves in today."},{"time":786000,"text":"From Lebanon he went to Bosnia in the '90s."},{"time":789000,"text":"The issues were, of course, ethnic sectarian violence."},{"time":793000,"text":"He was the first person to negotiate with the Khmer Rouge."},{"time":796000,"text":"Talk about evil prevailing. I mean, here he was in the room"},{"time":799000,"text":"with the embodiment of evil in Cambodia."},{"time":801000,"text":"He negotiates with the Serbs."},{"time":803000,"text":"He actually crosses so far into this realm of talking to evil"},{"time":807000,"text":"and trying to convince evil that it doesn't need to prevail"},{"time":810000,"text":"that he earns the nickname -- not Sergio but Serbio"},{"time":813000,"text":"while he's living in the Balkans and conducting these kinds of negotiations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818000,"text":"He then goes to Rwanda and to Congo in the aftermath of the genocide,"},{"time":821000,"text":"and he's the guy who has to decide -- huh, OK, the genocide is over;"},{"time":824000,"text":"800,000 people have been killed; the people responsible are fleeing"},{"time":828000,"text":"into neighboring countries -- into Congo, into Tanzania."},{"time":831000,"text":"I'm Sergio, I'm a humanitarian, and I want to feed those --"},{"time":834000,"text":"well, I don't want to feed the killers"},{"time":836000,"text":"but I want to feed the two million people who are with them, so we're going to go,"},{"time":839000,"text":"we're going to set up camps,"},{"time":841000,"text":"and we're going to supply humanitarian aid."},{"time":843000,"text":"But, uh-oh, the killers are within the camps."},{"time":846000,"text":"Well, I'd like to separate the sheep from the wolves."},{"time":848000,"text":"Let me go door-to-door to the international community"},{"time":850000,"text":"and see if anybody will give me police or troops to do the separation."},{"time":853000,"text":"And their response, of course, was no more than we wanted"},{"time":856000,"text":"to stop the genocide and put our troops in harm's way to do that,"},{"time":859000,"text":"nor do we now want to get in the way and pluck genocidaires from camps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"So then you have to make the decision."},{"time":866000,"text":"Do you turn off the international spigot of life support"},{"time":868000,"text":"and risk two million civilian lives?"},{"time":872000,"text":"Or do you continue feeding the civilians, knowing that the genocidaires"},{"time":875000,"text":"are in the camps, literally sharpening their knives for future battle?"},{"time":879000,"text":"What do you do?"},{"time":880000,"text":"It's all lesser-evil terrain in these broken places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883000,"text":"Late '90s: nation-building is the cause du jour."},{"time":886000,"text":"He's the guy put in charge. He's the Paul Bremer or the Jerry Bremer"},{"time":890000,"text":"of first Kosovo and then East Timor. He governs the places."},{"time":893000,"text":"He's the viceroy. He has to decide on tax policy, on currency,"},{"time":897000,"text":"on border patrol, on policing. He has to make all these judgments."},{"time":901000,"text":"He's a Brazilian in these places. He speaks seven languages."},{"time":904000,"text":"He's been up to that point in 14 war zones"},{"time":906000,"text":"so he's positioned to make better judgments, perhaps,"},{"time":909000,"text":"than people who have never done that kind of work."},{"time":911000,"text":"But nonetheless, he is the cutting edge of our experimentation"},{"time":915000,"text":"with doing good with very few resources being brought to bear in,"},{"time":918000,"text":"again, the world's worst places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920000,"text":"And then after Timor, 9/11 has happened,"},{"time":923000,"text":"he's named U.N. Human Rights Commissioner,"},{"time":925000,"text":"and he has to balance liberty and security and figure out,"},{"time":928000,"text":"what do you do when the most powerful country in the United Nations"},{"time":931000,"text":"is bowing out of the Geneva Conventions,"},{"time":934000,"text":"bowing out of international law? Do you denounce?"},{"time":936000,"text":"Well, if you denounce,"},{"time":937000,"text":"you're probably never going to get back in the room."},{"time":939000,"text":"Maybe you stay reticent. Maybe you try to charm President Bush --"},{"time":944000,"text":"and that's what he did. And in so doing he earned himself,"},{"time":947000,"text":"unfortunately, his final and tragic appointment to Iraq --"},{"time":950000,"text":"the one that resulted in his death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"One note on his death, which is so devastating,"},{"time":955000,"text":"is that despite predicating the war on Iraq"},{"time":957000,"text":"on a link between Saddam Hussein and terrorism in 9/11,"},{"time":962000,"text":"believe it or not, the Bush administration or the invaders"},{"time":965000,"text":"did no planning, no pre-war planning, to respond to terrorism."},{"time":969000,"text":"So Sergio -- this receptacle of all of this learning on how to deal with evil"},{"time":973000,"text":"and how to deal with brokenness,"},{"time":975000,"text":"lay under the rubble for three and a half hours without rescue."},{"time":979000,"text":"Stateless. The guy who tried to help the stateless people his whole career."},{"time":983000,"text":"Like a refugee. Because he represents the U.N."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"If you represent everyone, in some ways you represent no one."},{"time":988000,"text":"You're un-owned."},{"time":990000,"text":"And what the American -- the most powerful military in the history of mankind"},{"time":993000,"text":"was able to muster for his rescue,"},{"time":995000,"text":"believe it or not, was literally these heroic two American soldiers"},{"time":999000,"text":"went into the shaft. Building was shaking."},{"time":1001000,"text":"One of them had been at 9/11 and lost his buddies on September 11th,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"and yet went in and risked his life in order to save Sergio."},{"time":1007000,"text":"But all they had was a woman's handbag --"},{"time":1011000,"text":"literally one of those basket handbags --"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and they tied it to a curtain rope from one of the offices at U.N. headquarters,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"and created a pulley system into this shaft in this quivering building"},{"time":1022000,"text":"in the interests of rescuing this person,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"the person we most need to turn to now, this shepherd,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"at a time when so many of us feel like we're lacking guidance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031000,"text":"And this was the pulley system. This was what we were able to muster for Sergio."},{"time":1034000,"text":"The good news, for what it's worth,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"is after Sergio and 21 others were killed that day in the attack on the U.N.,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"the military created a search and rescue unit"},{"time":1042000,"text":"that had the cutting equipment, the shoring wood, the cranes,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"the things that you would have needed to do the rescue."},{"time":1048000,"text":"But it was too late for Sergio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050000,"text":"I want to wrap up, but I want to close"},{"time":1052000,"text":"with what I take to be the four lessons from Sergio's life"},{"time":1056000,"text":"on this question of how do we prevent evil from prevailing,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"which is how I would have framed the question."},{"time":1062000,"text":"Here's this guy who got a 34-year head start"},{"time":1065000,"text":"thinking about the kinds of questions we as a country are grappling with,"},{"time":1069000,"text":"we as citizens are grappling with now. What do we take away?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074000,"text":"First, I think, is his relationship to, in fact, evil is something to learn from."},{"time":1079000,"text":"He, over the course of his career, changed a great deal."},{"time":1082000,"text":"He had a lot of flaws, but he was very adaptive."},{"time":1084000,"text":"I think that was his greatest quality."},{"time":1086000,"text":"He started as somebody who would denounce harmdoers,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"he would charge up to people who were violating international law,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"and he would say, you're violating, this is the U.N. Charter."},{"time":1095000,"text":"Don't you see it's unacceptable what you're doing?"},{"time":1097000,"text":"And they would laugh at him because he didn't have the power of states,"},{"time":1100000,"text":"the power of any military or police."},{"time":1102000,"text":"He just had the rules, he had the norms, and he tried to use them."},{"time":1105000,"text":"And in Lebanon, Southern Lebanon in '82,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"he said to himself and to everybody else,"},{"time":1111000,"text":"I will never use the word \"unacceptable\" again."},{"time":1114000,"text":"I will never use it. I will try to make it such,"},{"time":1116000,"text":"but I will never use that word again."},{"time":1118000,"text":"But he lunged in the opposite direction."},{"time":1120000,"text":"He started, as I mentioned, to get in the room with evil,"},{"time":1123000,"text":"to not denounce, and became almost obsequious"},{"time":1127000,"text":"when he won the nickname Serbio, for instance,"},{"time":1130000,"text":"and even when he negotiated with the Khmer Rouge"},{"time":1132000,"text":"would black-box what had occurred prior to entering the room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1136000,"text":"But by the end of his life, I think he had struck a balance"},{"time":1139000,"text":"that we as a country can learn from."},{"time":1141000,"text":"Be in the room, don't be afraid of talking to your adversaries,"},{"time":1145000,"text":"but don't bracket what happened before you entered the room."},{"time":1149000,"text":"Don't black-box history. Don't check your principles at the door."},{"time":1154000,"text":"And I think that's something that we have to be in the room,"},{"time":1157000,"text":"whether it's Nixon going to China or Khrushchev and Kennedy"},{"time":1161000,"text":"or Reagan and Gorbachev."},{"time":1163000,"text":"All the great progress in this country with relation to our adversaries"},{"time":1167000,"text":"has come by going into the room."},{"time":1169000,"text":"And it doesn't have to be an act of weakness."},{"time":1172000,"text":"You can actually do far more to build an international coalition"},{"time":1175000,"text":"against a harmdoer or a wrongdoer by being in the room"},{"time":1178000,"text":"and showing to the rest of the world that that person, that regime,"},{"time":1181000,"text":"is the problem and that you, the United States, are not the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184000,"text":"Second take-away from Sergio's life, briefly."},{"time":1188000,"text":"What I take away, and this in some ways is the most important,"},{"time":1190000,"text":"he espoused and exhibited a reverence for dignity"},{"time":1196000,"text":"that was really, really unusual."},{"time":1198000,"text":"At a micro level, the individuals around him were visible."},{"time":1202000,"text":"He saw them."},{"time":1203000,"text":"At a macro level, he thought, you know,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"we talk about democracy promotion, but we do it in a way sometimes"},{"time":1208000,"text":"that's an affront to people's dignity."},{"time":1211000,"text":"We put people on humanitarian aid"},{"time":1213000,"text":"and we boast about it because we've spent three billion."},{"time":1215000,"text":"It's incredibly important,"},{"time":1216000,"text":"those people would no longer be alive if the United States, for instance,"},{"time":1218000,"text":"hadn't spent that money in Darfur,"},{"time":1221000,"text":"but it's not a way to live."},{"time":1222000,"text":"If we think about dignity in our conduct as citizens"},{"time":1225000,"text":"and as individuals with relation to the people around us,"},{"time":1228000,"text":"and as a country, if we could inject a regard for dignity"},{"time":1230000,"text":"into our dealings with other countries,"},{"time":1233000,"text":"it would be something of a revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1235000,"text":"Third point, very briefly. He talked a lot about freedom from fear."},{"time":1239000,"text":"And I recognize there is so much to be afraid of."},{"time":1242000,"text":"There are so many genuine threats in the world."},{"time":1244000,"text":"But what Sergio was talking about is,"},{"time":1246000,"text":"let's calibrate our relationship to the threat."},{"time":1248000,"text":"Let's not hype the threat; let's actually see it clearly."},{"time":1251000,"text":"We have reason to be afraid of melting ice caps."},{"time":1254000,"text":"We have reason to be afraid that we haven't secured"},{"time":1257000,"text":"loose nuclear material in the former Soviet Union."},{"time":1260000,"text":"Let's focus on what are the legitimate challenges and threats,"},{"time":1264000,"text":"but not lunge into bad decisions because of a panic, of a fear."},{"time":1269000,"text":"In times of fear, for instance, one of the things Sergio used to say"},{"time":1271000,"text":"is, fear is a bad advisor."},{"time":1273000,"text":"We lunge towards the extremes"},{"time":1275000,"text":"when we aren't operating and trying to, again,"},{"time":1277000,"text":"calibrate our relationship to the world around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1279000,"text":"Fourth and final point: he somehow, because he was working"},{"time":1282000,"text":"in all the world's worst places and all lesser evils,"},{"time":1285000,"text":"had a humility, of course,"},{"time":1287000,"text":"and an awareness of the complexity of the world around him."},{"time":1290000,"text":"I mean, such an acute awareness of how hard it was."},{"time":1292000,"text":"How Sisyphean this task was of mending,"},{"time":1296000,"text":"and yet aware of that complexity, \n"},{"time":1298000,"text":"humbled by it, he wasn't paralyzed by it."},{"time":1301000,"text":"And we as citizens, as we go through this experience of the kind of,"},{"time":1306000,"text":"the crisis of confidence, crisis of competence, crisis of legitimacy,"},{"time":1310000,"text":"I think there's a temptation to pull back from the world and say,"},{"time":1313000,"text":"ah, Katrina, Iraq -- we don't know what we're doing."},{"time":1315000,"text":"We can't afford to pull back from the world."},{"time":1318000,"text":"It's a question of how to be in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1321000,"text":"And the lesson, I think,"},{"time":1322000,"text":"of the anti-genocide movement that I mentioned,"},{"time":1324000,"text":"that is a partial success but by no means"},{"time":1326000,"text":"has it achieved what it has set out to do --"},{"time":1329000,"text":"it'll be many decades, probably, before that happens --"},{"time":1332000,"text":"but is that if we want to see change, we have to become the change."},{"time":1336000,"text":"We can't rely upon our institutions to do the work"},{"time":1340000,"text":"of necessarily talking to adversaries on their own"},{"time":1344000,"text":"without us creating a space for that to happen,"},{"time":1346000,"text":"for having respect for dignity,"},{"time":1348000,"text":"and for bringing that combination of humility"},{"time":1350000,"text":"and a sort of emboldened sense of responsibility"},{"time":1353000,"text":"to our dealings with the rest of the world."},{"time":1355000,"text":"So will evil prevail? Is that the question?"},{"time":1357000,"text":"I think the short answer is: no, not unless we let it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1361000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1362000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}